message.content:
cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.LO, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the complexity of submonoids accepted by circular semi-flower automata.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the complexity of certain types of submonoids.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper investigates the syntactic complexity of CSFA.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) may be relevant as the paper deals with formal languages and automata theory.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) may be relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of CSFA over a binary alphabet.
